{
  "texts": [
    "This meta-level automation transforms prompt engineering from manual design into a data-driven search and optimization process, providing a new pathway for enhancing LLM performance and lowering usage barriers.",
    "Fine-tuningWhile prompt engineering offers significant flexibility, it often struggles to handle highly specialized domain knowledge, such as financial rules or specific frameworks, due to constraints on context windows and reasoning capabilities.",
    "This limitation has motivated researchers to turn to finetuning strategies to achieve deeper knowledge internalization.",
    "In contrast to the external guidance provided by prompt engineering, fine-tuning achieves deep domain adaptation by updating model parameters.",
    "In the context of unit test generation, fine-tuning is typically modeled as a sequenceto-sequence (Seq2Seq) learning task, aiming to establish a mapping from code context (Source) to canonical test cases (Target).To systematically analyze this strategy, we decompose the fine-tuning process into three core dimensions."
  ]
}